wiki.summary: “Crush Em” previously known as “Own Age” through the series of snippets, is the 4th track on Pink Tape made by Philadelphia rapper Lil Uzi Vert. This song was rumored to be produced by Oogie Mane but apparently this wasn’t true at all. Also there was other rumors that this is the song URU (@UziRareUpdates) was talking about ‘Crush it / Warriors’, which -except the first part- isn’t completely true. It was rumored to be on the December 2022 Pink Tape tracklist however. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Crush Em” previously known as “Own Age” through the series of snippets, is the 4th track on Pink Tape made by Philadelphia rapper Lil Uzi Vert. This song was rumored to be produced by Oogie Mane but apparently this wasn’t true at all. Also there was other rumors that this is the song URU (@UziRareUpdates) was talking about ‘Crush it / Warriors’, which -except the first part- isn’t completely true. It was rumored to be on the December 2022 Pink Tape tracklist however. In the meantime, we used to think about this song’s name is either “Crush Em'/it” or “Warriors.” First snippet of this track would surface online on June 17, 2023, with other snippets belong to “Pluto to Mars.” Second snippet came out later on June 17, 2023 with an special audio watermark -belongs to a leaker- repeating over, “Don’t leak album songs,” which kinda confirmed we get an official release of this song on Pink Tape. And finally we have it! Read more on Last.fm. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License; additional terms may apply.
